List Users

Returns all users from the Dynizer.
By default all rows are returned. Optionally a window can be provided to fetch just a specific sub-set of rows to support pagination.

Authorizations:
JWT
query Parameters
window.limit
required
integer <int64>

Defines how many records at max are returned.
If fewer records are available, all will be returned.
Setting this to -1 will be interpreted as no limit

window.offset
required
integer <int64>

Defines the offset at which to start reading.
An offset of 0 will bean to start from the first possible record.

window.relative
boolean

The Dynizer keeps track of the last read position, this flag indicates wether the offset is relative to the current read position or absolute.

Responses

https://*.dynizer.com/api/v2/users

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
  • default
Content type
application/json
{
  • "total_users": 0,
  • "users": [
    • {
      • "user_name": "string",
      • "roles": [
        • {
          • "name": "string"
          }
        ],
      • "enabled": true
      }
    ]
}

ActionTypes

Delete ActionSchema

A ActionSchema can only be deleted if no Actions are defined.
If the ActionType has Actions and cascade is not set to true and Error will be returned.
The cascade flag can be used to mark the Actions and all its Instances as deleted.

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
action_schema_name
required
string

The current name of the ActionSchema to be deleted.

query Parameters
cascade
boolean

This flag allows to mark all associated Actions and Instances as deleted.
If cascade == false an error is raised if this ActionSchema has Actions and Instances.
ActionSchema with no Actions can be deleted no matter what value cascade has.

Responses

https://*.dynizer.com/api/v2/actionschemas/{action_schema_name}

Response samples

  • 200
  • 401
  • 500
  • default
Content type
application/json
{ }

Actions

Create Action

Creates an Action with the provided name.
The name needs to be unique, the CheckActionName call can be used to verify this.
The name can not start or end with a whitespace character.
The name can not contain any control characters at any position.

Authorizations:
JWT
Request Body schema: application/json
required

This is used to create an Action.
If supplied ActionLabels can be addes as well.
The if_not_exists flag allows if set not to raise an error if the Action already exists.

action_name
required
string

The unique name for the Action.
Use the CheckActionName, call to verify the name, without trying to create it.

if_not_exists
boolean

if set to true -> NO ERROR is returned if a Action by the provided name already exists in the system.
Any ActionLabels provided are IGNORED when if_not_exists == true and the Action already existed.

Array of objects (ActionLabel)

This allows to create the ActionLabels for the newly created Action in one go.

Responses

https://*.dynizer.com/api/v2/actions

  • "if_not_exists": true,
  • "action_labels": [

      • "component": "InvalidComponentType",
      • "default_data_type": "InvalidDataType",
      • "min_occurrence": 0,
      • "max_occurrence": 0,

Add ActionLabel

Adds an ActionLabel to an existing Action.
Use the CheckActionLabelName call to verify that the ActionLabel name can be added.

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
action_name
required
string

The unique name for the Action.
Use the CheckActionName, call to verify the name, without trying to create it.

Request Body schema: application/json
required
if_not_exists
boolean

if set to true -> NO ERROR is returned if a Action already has an ActionLabel by the provided name.
No changes to the ActionLabel will be performed when if_not_exists == true and the ActionLabel already exists.

action_label_name
required
string

The unique name of the ActionLabel within the **Action.
Use the CheckActionLabelName, call to verify the name, without creating it.

component
required
string (ComponentType)
Default: "InvalidComponentType"
Enum: "InvalidComponentType" "Who" "What" "Where" "When"
  • Who: subject data category
  • What: object data category
  • Where: spatial data category
  • When: temporal data category
default_data_type
required
string (DataType)
Default: "InvalidDataType"
Enum: "InvalidDataType" "DT_Integer" "DT_String" "DT_Boolean" "DT_Decimal" "DT_Timestamp" "DT_Uri" "DT_Void" "DT_Float" "DT_UnsignedInteger" "DT_Binary" "DT_Uuid" "DT_Text" "DT_Blob" "DT_Clob" "DT_Document" "DT_Any" "DT_Delete"
  • DT_Integer: Integer
  • DT_String: String
  • DT_Boolean: Boolean
  • DT_Decimal: Decimal fixed
  • DT_Timestamp: Timestamp
  • DT_Uri: URI
  • DT_Void: VOID is a designated DataType to indicate no value
  • DT_Float: Float
  • DT_UnsignedInteger: UInt
  • DT_Binary: Byte Array

Dynizer Query

SELECT to retrieve instances.

JWT
Request Body schema: application/json
required

dql
required
string

Array of objects (DynizerQueryParameter)

The DQL parameters.

statement
string

The name of the statement. The statement is not usable outside of SimpleQuery. Omitting this parameter sets the unnamed statement, which is not safe for concurrent usage within a session. Provide a unique statement name for concurrent queries within a session.

portal
string

The name of the portal. The portal is not usable outside of SimpleQuery. Omitting this parameter sets the unnamed portal, which is not safe for concurrent usage within a session. Provide a unique portal name for concurrent queries within a session.

Query Result Next

Reads ResultRows from a ResultHandle.
By default no rows are returned. A window must be provided to fetch just a specific sub-set of rows.

Authorizations:
JWT
path Parameters
result_handle
required
string

The unique identifier for the DQL Result to read from.

query Parameters
window.limit
required
integer <int64>

Defines how many records at max are returned.
If fewer records are available, all will be returned.
Setting this to -1 will be interpreted as no limit

window.offset
required
integer <int64>

Defines the offset at which to start reading.
An offset of 0 will bean to start from the first possible record.

window.relative
boolean

The Dynizer keeps track of the last read position, this flag indicates wether the offset is relative to the current read position or absolute.

Responses

https://*.dynizer.com/api/v2/query/{result_handle}/next

Create Object

Creates a reference URI value in the Dynizer which is needed to upload a large value of type TEXT, CLOB, BLOB or DOCUMENT.
TEXT is the DataType which will get indexed by the FullTextIndex if enabled.
CLOB is a charatecr LOB, unindexed large string
BLOB is a binary LOB, unindexed bytes
DOCUMENT is the JSON structured output of document analysis.

  • ODT_Text: object is of type TEXT, which can be indexed by the FullTextIndex
  • ODT_Blob: object is of type binary
  • ODT_Clob: object is of type character
  • ODT_Document: object is of type character, indexed by FullTextIndex
